    "updated_at": "2016-08-12T11:34:29Z",
    "body": "For capturing the window messages, you can find an example at `NativeWindowViews::PreHandleMSG`.\n\nBut hooking to `WM_PAINT` is just a very minor step to fully it, the pages are GPU accelerated and drew in another process, you have to make the painting works well with GPU acceleration while avoiding dragging down performance. After that you need to handle various mouse events and change the drawing accordingly, then translate the clicks into messages.\n\nI would consider this as super hard.\n\nA more practical way is to provide an API in JavaScript to return the painted bitmap of the buttons, and then handle the drawing and mouse events in web pages.\n"
  },
