    "updated_at": "2017-03-16T08:01:46Z",
    "body": "Hi! Very interesting project, I was struggling to obtain the same effect! There are so many options, but yours (re-directing the HTMENU area where you want, keeping the menus non-client stuff) seems the most promising. \r\nRegarding your last point: it's not that difficult, you can subclass the chromium wndproc and insert your message handlers. See what they are doing there (they left the menu where they are, but wrote a \"dark windows\" classes which can be applied to any hwnd, via subclassing: https://github.com/adobe/brackets-shell"
